messages.content:
Add file-based task brief support to the `delegate_task` MCP tool in `src/mcp-server.ts`.

## Background

Currently `delegate_task` sends the full task content inline in the bus message. For large task specs this bloats the worker's conversation context. The fix: when the orchestrator opts in, write the task brief to `.synapse/tasks/<activityId>.md` and send a short bus message with a file path reference instead.

## Changes required

### 1. `src/mcp-server.ts` â€” `delegate_task` handler (around line 556)

Add optional `task_file?: boolean` parameter to the tool schema (in the `inputSchema.properties` block for `delegate_task`, around line 313â€“330):

```json
"task_file": {
  "type": "boolean",
  "description": "If true, write the task content to .synapse/tasks/<activityId>.md and send a short reference message instead of the full content inline. Use for large task specs (>~300 tokens).",
  "default": false
}
```

In the handler (around line 556â€“565), after computing `activityId`, add the file-writing branch:

```typescript
if (task_file) {
  const tasksDir = join(process.cwd(), '.synapse', 'tasks');
  mkdirSync(tasksDir, { recursive: true });
  const briefPath = join(tasksDir, `${activityId}.md`);
  writeFileSync(briefPath, content, 'utf8');
  const preview = content.split('\n').slice(0, 3).join('\n');
  const shortMsg = `Task brief at .synapse/tasks/${activityId}.md\n\n${preview}${content.split('\n').length > 3 ? '\nâ€¦' : ''}`;
  sendMessage(AGENT_ID, to_id, shortMsg, priority);
} else {
  sendMessage(AGENT_ID, to_id, content, priority);
}
```

Note: `mkdirSync` and `writeFileSync` are already available from Node's `fs` module â€” check existing imports at the top of the file and add if needed.

### 2. `.synapse/tasks/` directory â€” add to `.gitignore`

Check if there's a `.gitignore` at the project root. If it already has `.synapse/` listed (which it likely does from `synapse init`), task files are already covered. If not, add `.synapse/tasks/` explicitly. Just check and report what you find â€” don't change `.gitignore` if `.synapse/` is already excluded.

### 3. Protocol doc â€” `.synapse/SYNAPSE-orchestrator.md`

Add a short note in the `delegate_task` section (or wherever task dispatch is documented) explaining the `task_file` option and when to use it. Something like:

> For large task specs (more than ~300 tokens), pass `task_file: true` to `delegate_task`. The brief will be written to `.synapse/tasks/<activityId>.md` and the worker will receive a short message with the file path. Workers: when your task message references a `.synapse/tasks/` file, read it with the `Read` tool before starting work.

## Key files
- `src/mcp-server.ts` â€” main change (tool schema + handler)
- `.gitignore` â€” check only, add `.synapse/tasks/` if needed
- `.synapse/SYNAPSE-orchestrator.md` â€” protocol doc addition

After implementing, run `npm run build` (or `tsc`) to verify clean compile, then call `report_done` with a summary of what changed.
